==================================================
AGENTS.md
==================================================

Generate:

AGENTS.md


Content:

This repository uses Tasker.

Before working:

1. Read .tasker/START.md

2. Read .tasker/current/WORKSPACE.md if it exists

3. Read .tasker/instructions.md

All important communication must happen through:

- declaration.md
- result.md
- status.json


Never leave undocumented changes.


==================================================
START.md
==================================================

Create:

.tasker/START.md


Purpose:

Universal protocol for any agent.

It must explain:

- how tasks work
- where instructions are
- where current work exists
- how agents communicate


Any AI agent should understand the project by reading this file.


==================================================
PROJECT INSTRUCTIONS
==================================================

Command:

tasker instructions


Opens:

.tasker/instructions.md


This contains project-wide rules.


Example:

Architecture:

Frontend:
React

Backend:
Go


Rules:

- add tests
- do not break APIs
- follow existing patterns


Every agent receives this.


==================================================
AGENT RULES
==================================================

Create:

.tasker/agent.md


Defines agent behavior.


Rules:

Before work:

- read task.md
- read instructions.md
- read declaration.md
- read current workspace


During work:

- update declaration.md


After work:

- update result.md
- update status.json


No undocumented changes.


==================================================
TASK MODEL
==================================================

A task is a folder.

Example:

.tasker/tasks/001-authentication/


Contains:


task.md

Goal and requirements.


instructions.md

Task-specific rules.


declaration.md

Agent handoff document.


status.json

Current state.


context.json

Generated context.


result.md

Final report.



==================================================
CREATE TASK
==================================================

Command:

tasker new


Opens editor.

Creates:

.tasker/tasks/001-name/


Use:

$EDITOR


Support:

- vim
- nano
- VS Code
- Cursor


==================================================
TASK HIERARCHY
==================================================

Tasks support unlimited nesting.

There is NO depth limit.


Example:


Authentication

    Research JWT

    Backend

        Middleware

            JWT parser

                Token validation

                    Expiration check



Filesystem:


001-auth/

    children/

        002-research/

        003-backend/

            children/

                004-middleware/

                    children/

                        005-parser/

                            children/

                                006-expiration/



Every task can have:

parent

children


Store relationships in metadata.


