==================================================
AGENT WORKSPACE
==================================================

Main command:


tasker checkout <task>


This prepares the environment.

Create:


.tasker/current/


Files:


WORKSPACE.md

FILES.md

CONTEXT.json



WORKSPACE.md contains:

Current task.

Parent tasks.

Instructions.

Relevant files.

References.

Memory results.

Expected output.



Example:


Current task:

Implement authentication middleware.


Rules:

Do not break API.


Relevant files:

src/auth.ts

src/router.ts


Previous decisions:

JWT selected.


Expected:

- middleware
- tests
- docs



==================================================
AGENT EXECUTION
==================================================

IMPORTANT:

Tasker must NOT depend on Claude or Codex.


Tasker is an agent-neutral protocol.


Optional helper:

tasker run


can launch agents.

But the filesystem protocol must work without it.


Agents supported:

- Claude
- Codex
- Cursor
- Aider
- future agents



==================================================
AGENT COMMUNICATION
==================================================

Every task has:


declaration.md


This is the main communication channel.


Example:


Status:

IN PROGRESS


Understanding:

Authentication uses JWT.


Completed:

Created middleware.


Files:

src/auth/middleware.go


Decisions:

Used middleware layer.

Reason:

Keep controllers unchanged.


Remaining:

Refresh tokens.


Next agent:

Continue refresh token implementation.



==================================================
AGENT SESSIONS
==================================================

Every agent run creates:


sessions/


Example:


sessions/

    001-agent-name/

        prompt.md

        response.md

        changes.json



Store:

- agent
- timestamp
- files changed
- decisions
- notes



==================================================
AGENT REPLACEMENT
==================================================

A new agent must be able to continue.


The new agent reads:


task.md

instructions.md

declaration.md

result.md

sessions/

git history



It must not need previous conversation history.


